    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Using this simple image widget you can display a clickable image in any sidebar.<\/p>\n<p>You can set the image to link to a URL of your choice or make it pop-up in a lightbox.<\/p>\n<p>The widget uses WordPress\\&#8217; built in media manager to provide you with a familiar interface for image upload\/selection.<\/p>\n<p>You can select the widget\\&#8217;s image size from the available drop-down menu which lists all available WordPress default image sizes.<\/p>\n",
        "installation": "<p>From within WordPress\\&#8217; dashboard:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to Plugins -&gt; Add New<\/li>\n<li>Search for \\&#8221;The Image Widget\\&#8221;<\/li>\n<li>Click \\&#8221;Install\\&#8221;<\/li>\n<li>Click \\&#8221;Activate\\&#8221;<\/li>\n<li>Go to <em>Appearance -&gt; Widgets<\/em> or <em>Customize -&gt; Widgets<\/em><\/li>\n<li>Drag the <em>The Image Widget<\/em> widget into the sidebar of your choice.<\/li>\n<li>Set the title, the link URL and select an image from your media library.<\/li>\n<li>Save and you are done.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Manually via FTP:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload the folder \\&#8217;ci-image-widget\/\\&#8217; into the \\&#8217;\/wp-content\/plugins\/\\&#8217; directory<\/li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the <em>Plugins<\/em> tab in WordPress<\/li>\n<li>Go to <em>Appearance -&gt; Widgets<\/em> or <em>Customize -&gt; Widgets<\/em><\/li>\n<li>Drag the <em>The Image Widget<\/em> widget into the sidebar of your choice.<\/li>\n<li>Set the title, the link URL and select an image from your media library.<\/li>\n<li>Save and you are done.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed a PHP notice thrown when updating the widget.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
